      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALLEVIATE (4) showed nice improvement at her second career start after having run well on debut at Kyneton by going to the front at Sale and coming right away to score by 2.25 lengths. Up to 1400m here shouldn't pose an issue and she draws for every chance. Expect she goes on with it. DECANTED (2) resumes. His form tapered off at the end of his first campaign but he showed good early promise in strong maidens behind city-performed horses. He can make his presence felt as a gelding. SPARKLING LUCK (1) won his maiden well enough two back, okay to the line in a bit of a dash home last time. He can push forward here and give a sight. CARDAMOM (5) resumes for her second campaign having won her maiden narrowly before a spell. She's won a jumpout leading in and might be able to go to a new level this time around. TITAN'S SPIRIT (3) won well at Pakenham when last seen and can measure up.",
